<question-stem>
<para> Why was the Alvarez team's 1980 paper important?<mediaExhibit frameType="mp3"
mediaRef="toeflPrac10228.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice> It disproved Edmond Halley's theories.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> It proved that the extinction of the dinosaurs was not caused
by a comet hitting Earth.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> It showed that dust from meteorite impacts could alter global
weather patterns.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> It produced the first firm evidence of a large-scale
meteorite impact on Earth around the time the dinosaurs became extinct.</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> The professor states the <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> famous paper </emphasis>by
Alvarez's team was the first time <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> hard evidence, </emphasis>or
firm evidence, was presented as support, so (D) is correct. The Alvarez paper
supported, not disproved Halley's theories, so (A) is contrary to fact. (B)
is also false, and (C) is not related to the Alvarez team's paper.</para>
</explanation>
